The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Thursday, July 01, 2004 				 Shipping Corp firmly anchored
 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT 																								Mumbai, June 30: Shipping Corporation of India (SCI) reported its highest ever net profit of Rs 626.99 crore for the fiscal ended March 31, 2004, up 128 per cent, compared with Rs 274.78 crore in the previous fiscal. This is the first time an Indian shipping company has recorded such a phenomenal growth.																								Net profit for the fourth quarter rose 102 per cent at Rs 257.14 crore over Rs 127.49 crore in the corresponding previous quarter. 																								The companys topline shot up to Rs 3,100.34 crore against Rs 2,376.51 crore a year earlier, while total income was at Rs 3,166.71 crore (Rs 2,446.50 crore).																								SCI said buoyant freight market during the year coupled with deliveries of new ships at the right time helped it notch up such good results. 																								Talking to reporters here today, P. K. Srivastava, chairman and managing director of SCI, said the company is no longer serving a limited market, instead, it is planning to tap the international business. 
